2	5	2025-09-03 08:00:25.445161	8	Action	update	---\nstep_id: 2\ntitle: AI Processing\ndescription: Run LLM + KN pipelines to decode and summarize content. Extract objectives,\n  insights, risks, and requirements; produce a structured TXT/Dbrief with references,\n  ready for validation and revision.\norder: 2\ncontent: "# CLIENT DBRIEF\\n\\n## Input Data\\n\\nSearch exclusively within the **KNOWLEDGE\n  REFERENCE BELOW** to extract the information required to populate the inputs marked\n  with `{{ }}` in the **Client Briefing Template: Igniting Great Brands**.  \\n\\nEvery\n  `{{ }}` placeholder must be filled with the clearest factual detail available in\n  the knowledge reference.  \\n- If multiple sources mention the same point, synthesize\n  them into one coherent answer.  \\n- If no information exists for a placeholder,\n  insert exactly: `\\"Information not explicitly available in provided data\\"`.  \\n\\n⚠️\n  Do **not** invent or infer content beyond the knowledge reference.  \\n⚠️ Do **not**\n  include metadata, source references, or citation markers.  \\n⚠️ The final output\n  must be delivered **exclusively in valid Markdown format**.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Tasks\\n\\n1.\n  **Populate the Template**  \\n   Replace all `{{ }}` fields in the \\"Client Briefing\n  Template: Igniting Great Brands\\" with factual content drawn strictly from the knowledge\n  reference.  \\n\\n2. **Briefing Quality Assessment**  \\n   Rate the quality and completeness\n  of the filled brief on a scale of 0–100. Provide a short justification, noting key\n  strengths and gaps.  \\n\\n3. **Required Additional Information**  \\n   List specific\n  questions or missing categories that should be requested from the client to fill\n  critical gaps.  \\n\\n4. **Complementary Research Recommendations**  \\n   Suggest\n  targeted areas of external research (e.g., market trends, cultural shifts, competitor\n  moves, audience insights) to strengthen the brief.  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Knowledge Referenc