12	5	2025-09-03 08:32:49.59128	135	Artifact	update	---\nid: 135\ntitle: 'CLIENT-INFO (EXECUTION #51)'\ncontent: "# Client Notes\\n\\n## 1. Client Overview\\n\\n- **Client Name:** Sinais do\n  Tempo  \\n- **Industry/Sector:** Comércio de materiais de acabamento e equipamentos\n  de luxo para arquitetura  \\n- **Business Size:** SME (cerca de 70 colaboradores;\n  faturação anual aproximada de €25M)  \\n- **Main Contact(s) & Decision Makers:**\n  António Pedro (CEO, antonio.pedro@sinaisdotempo.pt, +351 912 345 678)  \\n- **Date\n  of Initial Meeting:** 20/05/2025  \\n- **Our Team Attending:** Marta Silva (Brand\n  Strategist), João Ferreira (Creative Director), Ana Costa (Project Manager)  \\n\\n##\n  2. Project Essentials\\n\\n- **Type of Project:**  \\n  Criação de submarca monolítica\n  para materiais de wellness (SPAs), imagem de marca, website, redes sociais e design\n  system.  \\n\\n- **Primary Goals/Objectives:**  \\n  Apresentar-se como especialistas\n  no nicho de mercado dos SPAs e wellness, fornecimento e construção de spas privados\n  ou em hotéis.  \\n\\n- **Success Metrics/KPIs:**  \\n  - Reconhecimento da submarca\n  como especialista em wellness em até 12 meses.  \\n  - Aumento de 30% no volume de\n  leads qualificados vindos de arquitetos até 2026.  \\n  - 5 novos contratos com hotéis\n  ou clínicas de wellness até 2026.  \\n  - Crescimento de 20% em faturação na linha\n  de wellness até final de 2026.  \\n  - 15.000 seguidores segmentados nas redes sociais\n  no prazo de 1 ano.  \\n\\n- **Key Deadlines and Timelines:**  \\n  - Setembro 2025\n  → Início do projeto.  \\n  - Novembro 2025 → Conclusão da identidade visual.  \\n\n  \\ - Dezembro 2025 → Website multilíngue (PT/EN/ES) publicado.  \\n  - Janeiro 2026\n  → Primeira campanha digital ativa.  \\n  - Abril 2026 → Primeira avaliação de KPIs.\n  \\ \\n  - Expansão Espanha → início em 2027.  \\n\\n- **Anticipated Project Start Date:**\n  \\ \\n  Setembro de 2025  \\n\\n- **Market Entry:**  \\n  Primeira fase em Portugal (Lisboa,\n  Porto e Algarve), com expansão para Espanha até 2027.  \\n\\n- **Estimated Budget:**\n  \\ \\n  €250.000 (Branding, website, gestão de redes sociais por 12 meses, campanhas\n  digitais de lançamento).  \\n\\n- **Deliverables:**  \\n  - Identidade visual (logótipo,\n  paleta cromática, tipografia, manual de marca).  \\n  - Website multilíngue responsivo.\n  \\ \\n  - Perfis oficiais em Instagram, LinkedIn e YouTube.  \\n  - Design system unificado\n  (digital e offline).  \\n  - Guidelines de comunicação e conteúdo.  \\n  - Vídeo institucional\n  e campanha de lançamento.  \\n\\n## 3. Context and Background\\n\\n- **Current Situation:**\n  \\ \\n  Alinhados com a tendência internacional, estão a verificar um crescimento\n  acentuado da área de wellness, o que pode vir a representar uma boa fatia da faturação.\n  Querem ser vistos como especialistas em SPAs e wellness.  \\n\\n- **Why this project\n  now?**  \\n  Estão a antecipar o aparecimento de concorrência especializada nesta\n  área, o que lhes tiraria mercado. Por isso, querem tomar a dianteira e assumir-se\n  como pioneiros na especialização do mercado de spas de luxo em Portugal.  \\n\\n-\n  **Key Business Challenges:**  \\n  Dificuldade em comunicar expertise exclusiva em\n  SPAs de luxo dentro de uma marca generalista; necessidade de atrair investidores\n  e parceiros internacionais.  \\n\\n## 4. Brand Insight\\n\\n- **Existing Brand Positioning\n  and Perception:**  \\n  O mercado português tem 3 concorrentes diretos num segmento\n  médio e médio-alto. A Sinais do Tempo atua exclusivamente no mercado de luxo. Pela\n  natureza do produto, mesmo clientes com grande poder de compra podem optar por opções\n  menos premium, considerando a expectativa de utilização.  \\n\\n- **Desired Brand\n  Positioning (Future State):**  \\n  Especializados em SPAs de luxo.  \\n\\n- **Strengths\n  and Weaknesses of Current Brand:**  \\n  A marca mãe, Sinais do Tempo, tem excelente\n  reputação junto de ateliers de arquitetura e clientes premium, mas é uma marca generalista\n  (vende puxadores, soalhos, janelas, roupeiros, sistemas de estantes, cadeiras e\n  equipamentos de jardim). Assim, não consegue ser percebida como especialista em\n  SPAs, o que justifica a criação de uma submarca monolítica focada neste segmento\n  para transmitir confiança e enfrentar melhor a concorrência.  \\n\\n- **Core Values,\n  Vision, and Mission:**  \\n  Qualidade máxima no serviço e no produto para satisfazer\n  o mercado mais exigente.  \\n  Missão: Criar experiências únicas através de ambientes\n  de wellness sofisticados.  \\n  Visão: Ser líder em soluções de spas de luxo na Península\n  Ibérica até 2030.  \\n\\n- **Creative Guidance:**  \\n  - Linguagem visual minimalista\n  e internacional.  \\n  - Paleta cromática: cinzas, brancos e pretos, com acentos\n  dourados.  \\n  - Tom de voz: aspiracional, sofisticado, confiável.  \\n  - Diretrizes\n  de uso de marca para digital e print.  \\n\\n- **Approval Process:**  \\n  1. Entregas\n  parciais submetidas ao marketing.  \\n  2. Feedback consolidado em até 5 dias úteis.\n  \\ \\n  3. Aprovação final pelo CEO e Conselho de Administração.  \\n\\n## 5. Audience\n  Definition\\n\\n- **Primary Audience:**  \\n  Ateliers de Arquitetura e clientes premium\n  portugueses com foco em lifestyle e bem-estar.  \\n\\n- **Secondary Audience:**  \\n\n  \\ Cadeias de hotéis, clínicas de wellness e particulares premium em Portugal e Espanha.\n  \\ \\n\\n- **Internal Stakeholders:**  \\n  Conselho de Administração, equipa de marketing,\n  equipa técnica de projetos  \\n\\n---\\n\\n# Client Audio Transcriptions\\n\\n## Audio\n  1\\nQuando fundei a Sinais do Tempo, o meu sonho era, claro, trazer para Portugal\n  o que há de mais inovador e refinado no design de interiores e na arquitetura. Ver\n  esse sonho ganhar forma em cada projeto concretizado é uma enorme satisfação. Mas\n  não ficamos por aqui. A nossa missão é continuar a surpreender, criando ambientes\n  que inspirem e transformem. A Sinais do Tempo é mais do que uma empresa de design,\n  é um legado em constante construção.\\n\\n## Audio 2\\nConheci a Sinais do Tempo através\n  da recomendação de um arquiteto e desde o primeiro contacto fiquei impressionado.\n  A qualidade dos produtos, o atendimento atento, o cuidado com cada pormenor. O meu\n  projeto residencial ganhou vida com soluções que eu nunca imaginei serem possíveis.\n  Hoje, a minha casa não é apenas bonita, ela reflete quem eu sou. A Sinais do Tempo\n  fez muito mais do que decorar um espaço. Compreenderam o meu estilo de vida e traduziram-no\n  em cada ambiente.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# Client Video Transcriptions\\n\\n## Video 1\\nEm Lisboa,\n  existe um espaço onde o design encontra a excelência, a Sinais do Tempo. Desde 2005,\n  representamos com exclusividade algumas das mais prestigiadas marcas internacionais\n  de arquitetura, design de interiores e construção. Com produtos assinados por nomes\n  como Rimadesio, Dada, Molteni e Lualdi, oferecemos soluções sofisticadas, tecnológicas\n  e elegantes para espaços residenciais e comerciais. Cada detalhe revela o nosso\n  compromisso com a inovação e a estética. Sinais do Tempo, onde o design transcende\n  o tempo.\\n\\n## Video 2\\nTransformar espaços é mais do que a nossa profissão, é a\n  nossa paixão. Com um portfólio completo de ambientes personalizados e materiais\n  de excelência, tornamos realidade os sonhos de quem procura beleza, conforto e funcionalidade.\n  Em cada projeto, traduzimos desejos em soluções únicas, alinhando forma e função\n  com elegância. Os nossos clientes não apenas decoram os seus espaços, eles contam\n  histórias. Sinais do Tempo. Mais do que design, uma experiência de vida. Finalizar\n  com o logótipo da Sinais do Tempo e a frase Mais do que design, uma experiência\n  de vida."\ncreated_at: 2025-09-03 08:32:18.019661000 -03:00\nupdated_at: 2025-09-03 08:32:49.591280000 -03:00\nresource_type: WorkflowExecution\nresource_id: 51\ncode: ART-1A572524\ndescription: Gather client inputs (text, PDFs, video, audio, links). Capture goals,\n  context, constraints, KPIs, and audience. Normalize formats (OCR/transcription),\n  deduplicate, tag sources, and ensure consent/compliance.\n	\N
13	5	2025-09-03 08:38:08.602166	8	Action	update	---\nstep_id: 2\ntitle: AI Processing\ndescription: Run LLM + KN pipelines to decode and summarize content. Extract objectives,\n  insights, risks, and requirements; produce a structured TXT/Dbrief with references,\n  ready for validation and revision.\norder: 2\ncontent: "# CLIENT DBRIEF\\n\\n## Knowledge Reference Requirement  \\n- Before executing\n  any research or analysis task, the AI must consult the session **CLIENT-INFO** as\n  the primary knowledge base.  \\n- Extract all relevant information about project\n  fundamentals, current brand and business assessment, branding challenges, audience\n  understanding, deliverables, creative guidance, and collaboration details from **CLIENT-INFO**\n  and integrate it as foundational reference.  \\n- Only when **CLIENT-INFO** lacks\n  sufficient detail, follow the Research Source Protocol (RAG sources first, web backup\n  second).  \\n- Always cross-validate **CLIENT-INFO** findings with external sources\n  to ensure confidence and applicability.  \\n\\n## Tasks\\n\\n1. **Briefing Quality Assessment**\n  \\ \\n   Rate the quality and completeness of the filled brief on a scale of 0–100.\n  Provide a short justification, noting key strengths and gaps.  \\n\\n2. **Required\n  Additional Information**  \\n   List specific questions or missing categories that\n  should be requested from the client to fill critical gaps.  \\n\\n3. **Complementary\n  Research Recommendations**  \\n   Suggest targeted areas of external research (e.g.,\n  market trends, cultural shifts, competitor moves, audience insights) to strengthen\n  the brief.  \\n\\n--- \\n\\n# Client Briefing Template: Igniting Great Brands\\n\\n##\n  1. Project & Client Fundamentals\\n- **Client Name:**  {{CLIENT NAME}}\\n- **Primary\n  Client Contact(s):** {{Name, Title, Email, Phone}}\\n- **Date of Meeting:**  {{DATE\n  OF MEETING}}\\n- **Our Team Attending:**  {{Our Team Attending}}\\n- **Project Name/Working\n  Title:**  {{PROJECT NAME}}\\n- **Anticipated Project Start Date:**  {{PROJECT START\n  DATE}}\\n- **Desired Project Completion Date/Key Milestones:**  {{PROJECT COMPLETION\n  DATE / KEY MILESTONES}}\\n- **Urgency/Key Drivers for Project:**  {{URGENCY / DRIVERS}}\\n-\n  **Client's Core Business/Offering:**  {{CORE BUSINESS}}\\n- **Company Size & Structure:**\n  \\ {{COMPANY SIZE / STRUCTURE}}\\n- **Key Stakeholders & Decision-Makers:**  {{STAKEHOLDERS}}\\n-\n  **Company Culture & Values:**  {{CULTURE / VALUES}}\\n\\n## 2. Current Brand & Business\n  Assessment\\n- **Current Business Performance/Health:**  {{CURRENT PERFORMANCE}}\\n-\n  **Current Brand Perception (Internal & External):**  {{BRAND PERCEPTION}}\\n- **Existing\n  Brand Assets & Equity:**  {{BRAND ASSETS}}\\n- **Pain Points with Current Brand Expression:**\n  \\ {{PAIN POINTS}}\\n- **Brand Heritage & Key Milestones:**  {{HERITAGE / MILESTONES}}\\n-\n  **Core Values, Vision, and Mission (if defined):**  {{VISION / MISSION / VALUES}}\\n\\n##\n  3. Defining the Branding Challenge & Opportunity\\n- **The Core Problem/Opportunity\n  We're Addressing:**  {{CORE PROBLEM / OPPORTUNITY}}\\n- **Specific Project Objectives:**\n  \\ {{OBJECTIVES}}\\n- **Success Metrics & KPIs:**  {{KPIS}}\\n- **Desired Brand Positioning\n  (Future State):**  {{POSITIONING}}\\n- **Key Message(s) to Convey:**  {{MESSAGES}}\\n\\n##\n  4. Audience & Market Understanding\\n- **Target Audience(s):**  {{TARGET AUDIENCES}}\\n-\n  **Primary Audience:**  {{PRIMARY AUDIENCE}}\\n- **Secondary Audience (if applicable):**\n  \\ {{SECONDARY AUDIENCE}}\\n- **Internal Stakeholders:**  {{INTERNAL STAKEHOLDERS}}\\n-\n  **Desired Audience Reaction (Think, Feel, Do):**  {{AUDIENCE REACTION}}\\n- **Competitive\n  Landscape:**  {{COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE}}\\n- **Market Trends & Cultural Factors:**\n  \\ {{MARKET TRENDS}}\\n- **Differentiation Potential & Brand Whitespace:**  {{DIFFERENTIATION}}\\n\\n##\n  5. Project Deliverables & Parameters\\n- **Type of Project:**  {{PROJECT TYPE}}\\n-\n  **Specific Deliverables Required:**  {{DELIVERABLES}}\\n- **Priority Deliverables:**\n  \\ {{PRIORITY DELIVERABLES}}\\n- **Budget Overview/Parameters:**  {{BUDGET}}\\n- **Timeline\n  Constraints & Critical Milestones:**  {{TIMELINE}}\\n- **Internal Approval Structures\n  & Decision-Making Process:**  {{APPROVAL STRUCTURES}}\\n- **Implementation Capabilities\n  & Constraints:**  {{IMPLEMENTATION CONSTRAINTS}}\\n\\n## 6. Tone, Style & Creative\n  Guidance\\n- **Desired Emotional Response:**  {{EMOTIONAL RESPONSE}}\\n- **Preferred\n  Brand Personality/Tone of Voice:**  {{TONE OF VOICE}}\\n- **Examples of Liked/Disliked\n  Brands, Styles, or Approaches (and why):**  {{LIKED / DISLIKED EXAMPLES}}\\n- **Brand\n  \\"Never-Use\\" Words or Themes:**  {{NEVER USE}}\\n- **Strategic Hypotheses/Initial\n  Directional Thinking:**  {{HYPOTHESES}}\\n\\n## 7. Next Steps & Collaboration\\n- **Immediate\n  Actions Post-Meeting:**  {{NEXT ACTIONS}}\\n- **Information Needed from Client:**\n  \\ {{INFO NEEDED}}\\n- **Client Availability and Involvement:**  {{CLIENT AVAILABILITY}}\\n-\n  **Follow-up Meeting Date (if applicable):**  {{FOLLOW UP}}\\n- **Any Additional Information/Questions\n  for Us:**  {{ADDITIONAL INFO}} \\n\\n---\\n\\n# KNOWLEDGE REFERENCE\\n<<SEARCHER>>\\n\n  \\  <<PROMPT-GENERATOR>>\\n      What is client #{client}'s name?  \\n      Who are\n  client #{client}'s primary contacts (name, title, email, phone)?  \\n      What is\n  the date of the meeting with client #{client}?  \\n      Who from our team attended\n  the meeting with client #{client}?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s project name\n  or working title?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s anticipated project start\n  date?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s desired project completion date or key\n  milestones?  \\n      What are client #{client}'s urgency factors or key drivers\n  for the project?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s core business or offering?\n  \\ \\n      What is client #{client}'s company size and structure?  \\n      Who are\n  client #{client}'s key stakeholders and decision-makers?  \\n      What is client\n  #{client}'s company culture and values?  \\n\\n      What is client #{client}'s current\n  business performance or health?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s current brand\n  perception (internal & external)?  \\n      What existing brand assets and equity\n  does client #{client} have?  \\n      What pain points does client #{client} face\n  with current brand expression?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s brand heritage\n  and key milestones?  \\n      What are client #{client}'s core values, vision, and\n  mission?  \\n\\n      What is the core problem or opportunity being addressed for\n  client #{client}?  \\n      What are client #{client}'s specific project objectives?\n  \\ \\n      What are client #{client}'s success metrics and KPIs?  \\n      What is\n  client #{client}'s desired brand positioning (future state)?  \\n      What key messages\n  should client #{client} convey?  \\n\\n      Who are client #{client}'s target audiences?\n  \\ \\n      Who is client #{client}'s primary audience?  \\n      Who is client #{client}'s\n  secondary audience (if applicable)?  \\n      Who are client #{client}'s internal\n  stakeholders?  \\n      What is the desired audience reaction (think, feel, do) for\n  client #{client}?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s competitive landscape?  \\n\n  \\     What market trends and cultural factors affect client #{client}?  \\n      What\n  is client #{client}'s differentiation potential or brand whitespace?  \\n\\n      What\n  type of project is client #{client} undertaking?  \\n      What specific deliverables\n  are required by client #{client}?  \\n      What are client #{client}'s priority\n  deliverables?  \\n      What is client #{client}'s budget overview or parameters?\n  \\ \\n      What timeline constraints and critical milestones exist for client #{client}?\n  \\ \\n      What are client #{client}'s internal approval structures and decision-making\n  process?  \\n      What implementation capabilities and constraints does client #{client}\n  have?  \\n\\n      What emotional response is desired for client #{client}'s brand?\n  \\ \\n      What is client #{client}'s preferred brand personality or tone of voice?\n  \\ \\n      What examples of liked or disliked brands, styles, or approaches does\n  client #{client} have (and why)?  \\n      What words or themes are \\"never-use\\"\n  for client #{client}'s brand?  \\n      What are client #{client}'s strategic hypotheses\n  or initial directional thinking?  \\n\\n      What are the immediate actions post-meeting\n  for client #{client}?  \\n      What information is still needed from client #{client}?\n  \\ \\n      What is client #{client}'s availability and involvement?  \\n      What\n  is the follow-up meeting date with client #{client} (if applicable)?  \\n      What\n  additional information or questions does client #{client} have for us?  \\n   <<PROMPT-GENERATOR>>\\n\\n\n  \\  <<ARTIFACT>>CLIENT-DBRIEF<<ARTIFACT>>\\n\\n<<SEARCHER>>"\nhas_ai_action: false\nhas_prompt_generator: true\nartifact_name: CLIENT-DBRIEF\nid: 8\ncreated_at: 2025-08-28 11:18:02.774469000 -03:00\nupdated_at: 2025-09-03 08:32:03.550640000 -03:00\n	---\nupdated_at:\n- 2025-09-03 08:32:03.550640000 -03:00\n- 2025-09-03 08:38:08.602166000 -03:00\ncontent:\n- "# CLIENT DBRIEF\\n\\n## Knowledge Reference Requirement  \\n- Before executing any\n  research or analysis task, the AI must consult the session **CLIENT-INFO** as the\n  primary knowledge base.  \\n- Extract all relevant information about project fundamentals,\n  current brand and business assessment, branding challenges, audience understanding,\n  deliverables, creative guidance, and collaboration details from **CLIENT-INFO**\n  and integrate it as foundational reference.  \\n- Only when **CLIENT-INFO** lacks\n  sufficient detail, follow the Research Source Protocol (RAG sources first, web backup\n  second).  \\n- Always cross-validate **CLIENT-INFO** findings with external sources\n  to ensure confidence and applicability.  \\n\\n## Tasks\\n\\n1. **Briefing Quality Assessment**\n  \\ \\n   Rate the quality and completeness of the filled brief on a scale of 0–100.\n  Provide a short justification, noting key strengths and gaps.  \\n\\n2. **Required\n  Additional Information**  \\n   List specific questions or missing categories that\n  should be requested from the client to fill critical gaps.  \\n\\n3. **Complementary\n  Research Recommendations**  \\n   Suggest targeted areas of external research (e.g.,\n  market trends, cultural shifts, competitor moves, audience insights) to strengthen\n  the brief.  \\n\\n--- \\n\\n# Client Briefing Template: Igniting Great Brands\\n\\n##\n  1. Project & Client Fundamentals\\n- **Client Name:**  {{CLIENT NAME}}\\n- **Primary\n  Client Contact(s):** {{Name, Title, Email, Phone}}\\n- **Date of Meeting:**  {{DATE\n  OF MEETING}}\\n- **Our Team Attending:**  {{Our Team Attending}}\\n- **Project Name/Working\n  Title:**  {{PROJECT NAME}}\\n- **Anticipated Project Start Date:**  {{PROJECT START\n  DATE}}\\n- **Desired Project Completion Date/Key Milestones:**  {{PROJECT COMPLETION\n  DATE / KEY MILESTONES}}\\n- **Urgency/Key Drivers for Project:**  {{URGENCY / DRIVERS}}\\n-\n  **Client's Core Business/Offering:**  {{CORE BUSINESS}}\\n- **Company Size & Structure:**\n  \\ {{COMPANY SIZE / STRUCTURE}}\\n- **Key Stakeholders & Decision-Makers:**  {{STAKEHOLDERS}}\\n-\n  **Company Culture & Values:**  {{CULTURE / VALUES}}\\n\\n## 2. Current Brand & Business\n  Assessment\\n- **Current Business Performance/Health:**  {{CURRENT PERFORMANCE}}\\n-\n  **Current Brand Perception (Internal & External):**  {{BRAND PERCEPTION}}\\n- **Existing\n  Brand Assets & Equity:**  {{BRAND ASSETS}}\\n- **Pain Points with Current Brand Expression:**\n  \\ {{PAIN POINTS}}\\n- **Brand