21	5	2025-09-03 10:24:03.82431	9	Action	update	---\nstep_id: 3\ntitle: PESTLE RESEARCH\ndescription: 'This prompt guides Perplexity to research recent branding-related PESTLE\n  insights for a specific product, audience, industry, and geography. It requires\n  short, factual answers with citations, focusing on brand perception, communication,\n  reputation, and social media trends. Sources must be reliable and recent (12–18\n  months), highlighting macro-environmental factors that influence brand positioning\n  and engagement.  '\norder: 1\ncontent: "# PESTLE Brand Research Assignment\\n\\n## Context & Methodology\\n\\nYou are\n  conducting a PESTLE analysis specifically through the lens of brand strategy and\n  consumer engagement. Your research must identify macro-environmental factors that\n  directly or indirectly influence brand perception, positioning opportunities, and\n  strategic communication.\\n\\n### Research Methodology:\\n1. **Source Diversity Requirements**:\n  \\ \\n   - Minimum 3 source types per PESTLE category from: industry reports, academic\n  research, news media (last 18 months), government data, trend forecasting firms,\n  consumer surveys, expert commentary  \\n   - Prioritize authoritative sources: McKinsey,\n  Forrester, Gartner, Pew Research, government statistics, peer-reviewed journals\n  \\ \\n   - Include both global perspectives and market-specific insights  \\n\\n2. **Temporal\n  Framing**:  \\n   - Current state: factors actively influencing the market now  \\n\n  \\  - Emerging (6-12 months): trends gaining momentum  \\n   - Future horizon (1-3\n  years): anticipated shifts requiring preparation  \\n\\n3. **Brand Impact Assessment**:\n  \\ \\n   Each insight must clearly connect to one or more of:  \\n   - Brand perception/reputation\n  \\ \\n   - Consumer behavior changes  \\n   - Communication channel evolution  \\n   -\n  Competitive differentiation opportunities  \\n   - Brand experience transformation\n  \\ \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Brand Specifications\\n\\n### Brand Identity\\n- **Brand Name**: {{Brand\n  Name}}  \\n- **Industry/Sector**: {{Industry/Sector}}  \\n- **Brand Archetype**: {{Brand\n  Archetype}}  \\n- **Core Values**: {{Core Values}}  \\n- **Brand Purpose/Mission**:\n  {{Brand Purpose/Mission}}  \\n\\n### Market Position\\n- **Target Segments**: {{Target\n  Segments}}  \\n- **Geographic Markets**: {{Geographic Markets}}  \\n- **Competitive\n  Set**: {{main_competitors}}  \\n- **Market Position**: {{Market Position: leader/challenger/niche}}\n  \\ \\n- **Price Positioning**: {{Price Positioning: premium/mid/value}}  \\n\\n### Strategic\n  Context\\n- **Current Brand Challenges**: {{Current Brand Challenges}}  \\n- **Growth\n  Objectives**: {{Growth Objectives}}  \\n- **Innovation Areas**: {{Innovation Areas}}\n  \\ \\n- **Brand Heritage/History**: {{Brand Heritage/History}}  \\n- **Sustainability\n  Commitments**: {{Sustainability Commitments}}  \\n\\n### Consumer Relationship\\n-\n  **Customer Journey Stage Focus**: {{Customer Journey Stage Focus: awareness/consideration/purchase/loyalty}}\n  \\ \\n- **Digital Maturity**: {{Digital Maturity: traditional/hybrid/digital-first}}\n  \\ \\n- **Community Engagement Level**: {{Community Engagement Level: passive/active/co-creative}}\n  \\ \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Request\\n\\n### Task Specifications:\\n⚠️ **Output Requirement**:\n  Deliver **exactly 120 insights in one single continuous response** (20 for each\n  PESTLE category). Do **not** ask for confirmation, do **not** split across responses,\n  and do **not** stop early. If necessary, compress formatting, but keep all insights\n  complete.\\n\\nGenerate **exactly 20 insights per PESTLE category** (120 total maximum)\n  that meet these criteria:\\n\\n#### For each insight, provide:\\n1. **Insight Title**:\n  Clear, specific descriptor [Opportunity/Threat] [Short-term: 0-1yr/Long-term: 1-3yr]\n  [Confidence: High/Medium/Low]  \\n2. **Detailed Paragraph** including:  \\n   - Specific\n  trend/factor description with quantitative data where available  \\n   - Direct brand\n  impact explanation  \\n   - Supporting evidence from named sources  \\n   - Geographic/demographic\n  specifics if applicable  \\n   - Connection to brand's strategic context  \\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n  POLITICAL FACTORS\\n\\n### P1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity | Short-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed\n  paragraph with evidence, brand impact, and strategic implications...]\\n\\n[Continue\n  P2–P20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ECONOMIC FACTORS\\n\\n### E1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity |\n  Long-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph with evidence, brand impact, and\n  strategic implications...]\\n\\n[Continue E2–E20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## SOCIAL FACTORS\\n\\n###\n  S1: [Insight Title] | Threat | Short-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph\n  with evidence, brand impact, and strategic implications...]\\n\\n[Continue S2–S20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n  TECHNOLOGICAL FACTORS\\n\\n### T1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity | Short-term | Medium\n  Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph with evidence, brand impact, and strategic implications...]\\n\\n[Continue\n  T2–T20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## LEGAL FACTORS\\n\\n### L1: [Insight Title] | Threat | Short-term\n  | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph with evidence, brand impact, and strategic\n  implications...]\\n\\n[Continue L2–L20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ENVIRONMENTAL FACTORS\\n\\n###\n  EN1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity | Long-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph\n  with evidence, brand impact, and strategic implications...]\\n\\n[Continue EN2–EN20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n  Research Metadata\\n- **Research Date**: {{Today's date}}  \\n- **Primary Markets\n  Analyzed**: {{List of Primary Markets Analyzed}}  \\n- **Key Sources Consulted**:\n  {{Key Sources Consulted: List top 10 sources}}  \\n\\n---\\n\\n### Quality Criteria:\\n-\n  Specificity over generalization  \\n- Evidence-based over speculative  \\n- Brand-relevant\n  over generic business impact  \\n- Actionable over merely informational  \\n- Current\n  and emerging over historical  \\n- ⚠️ The assistant must always return the **full\n  set of 120 insights in a single output**, never dividing across responses.\\n\\n\\n<<SEARCHER>>\\n\\n<<PROMPT>>\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Brand Name\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Industry/Sector\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Brand Archetype\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Core Values\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Brand Purpose/Mission\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Target Segments\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Geographic Markets\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Main Competitors\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Market Position: leader/challenger/niche\\nWhat is client #{client}'s\n  Price Positioning: premium/mid/value\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Current Brand Challenges\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Growth Objectives\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Innovation Areas\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Brand Heritage/History\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Sustainability\n  Commitments\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Customer Journey Stage Focus: awareness/consideration/purchase/loyalty\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Digital Maturity: traditional/hybrid/digital-first\\nWhat is\n  client #{client}'s Community Engagement Level: passive/active/co-creative\\n<<PROMPT>>\\n\\n<<PROMPT-GENERATOR>>\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Brand Name\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Industry/Sector\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Brand Archetype\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Core Values\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Brand Purpose/Mission\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Target Segments\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Geographic Markets\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Main Competitors\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Market Position: leader/challenger/niche\\nWhat is client #{client}'s\n  Price Positioning: premium/mid/value\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Current Brand Challenges\\nWhat\n  is client #{client}'s Growth Objectives\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Innovation A