munication.\\n\\n###\n  Research Methodology:\\n1. **Source Diversity Requirements**:  \\n   - Minimum 3 source\n  types per PESTLE category from: industry reports, academic research, news media\n  (last 18 months), government data, trend forecasting firms, consumer surveys, expert\n  commentary  \\n   - Prioritize authoritative sources: McKinsey, Forrester, Gartner,\n  Pew Research, government statistics, peer-reviewed journals  \\n   - Include both\n  global perspectives and market-specific insights  \\n\\n2. **Temporal Framing**:  \\n\n  \\  - Current state: factors actively influencing the market now  \\n   - Emerging\n  (6-12 months): trends gaining momentum  \\n   - Future horizon (1-3 years): anticipated\n  shifts requiring preparation  \\n\\n3. **Brand Impact Assessment**:  \\n   Each insight\n  must clearly connect to one or more of:  \\n   - Brand perception/reputation  \\n\n  \\  - Consumer behavior changes  \\n   - Communication channel evolution  \\n   - Competitive\n  differentiation opportunities  \\n   - Brand experience transformation  \\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n  Brand Specifications\\n\\n### Brand Identity\\n- **Brand Name**: {{Brand Name}}  \\n-\n  **Industry/Sector**: {{Industry/Sector}}  \\n- **Brand Archetype**: {{Brand Archetype}}\n  \\ \\n- **Core Values**: {{Core Values}}  \\n- **Brand Purpose/Mission**: {{Brand Purpose/Mission}}\n  \\ \\n\\n### Market Position\\n- **Target Segments**: {{Target Segments}}  \\n- **Geographic\n  Markets**: {{Geographic Markets}}  \\n- **Competitive Set**: {{main_competitors}}\n  \\ \\n- **Market Position**: {{Market Position: leader/challenger/niche}}  \\n- **Price\n  Positioning**: {{Price Positioning: premium/mid/value}}  \\n\\n### Strategic Context\\n-\n  **Current Brand Challenges**: {{Current Brand Challenges}}  \\n- **Growth Objectives**:\n  {{Growth Objectives}}  \\n- **Innovation Areas**: {{Innovation Areas}}  \\n- **Brand\n  Heritage/History**: {{Brand Heritage/History}}  \\n- **Sustainability Commitments**:\n  {{Sustainability Commitments}}  \\n\\n### Consumer Relationship\\n- **Customer Journey\n  Stage Focus**: {{Customer Journey Stage Focus: awareness/consideration/purchase/loyalty}}\n  \\ \\n- **Digital Maturity**: {{Digital Maturity: traditional/hybrid/digital-first}}\n  \\ \\n- **Community Engagement Level**: {{Community Engagement Level: passive/active/co-creative}}\n  \\ \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Request\\n\\n### Task Specifications:\\n⚠️ **Output Requirement**:\n  Deliver **exactly 120 insights in one single continuous response** (20 for each\n  PESTLE category). Do **not** ask for confirmation, do **not** split across responses,\n  and do **not** stop early. If necessary, compress formatting, but keep all insights\n  complete.\\n\\nGenerate **exactly 20 insights per PESTLE category** (120 total maximum)\n  that meet these criteria:\\n\\n#### For each insight, provide:\\n1. **Insight Title**:\n  Clear, specific descriptor [Opportunity/Threat] [Short-term: 0-1yr/Long-term: 1-3yr]\n  [Confidence: High/Medium/Low]  \\n2. **Detailed Paragraph** including:  \\n   - Specific\n  trend/factor description with quantitative data where available  \\n   - Direct brand\n  impact explanation  \\n   - Supporting evidence from named sources  \\n   - Geographic/demographic\n  specifics if applicable  \\n   - Connection to brand's strategic context  \\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n  POLITICAL FACTORS\\n\\n### P1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity | Short-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed\n  paragraph with evidence, brand impact, and strategic implications...]\\n\\n[Continue\n  P2–P20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ECONOMIC FACTORS\\n\\n### E1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity |\n  Long-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph with evidence, brand impact, and\n  strategic implications...]\\n\\n[Continue E2–E20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## SOCIAL FACTORS\\n\\n###\n  S1: [Insight Title] | Threat | Short-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph\n  with evidence, brand impact, and strategic implications...]\\n\\n[C