al\n  (P1–P20)  \\n- Economic (E1–E20)  \\n- Social (S1–S20)  \\n- Technological (T1–T20)  \\n-\n  Legal (L1–L20)  \\n- Environmental (EN1–EN20)  \\n\\u003c\\u003cPROMPT\\u003e\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c\\u003cARTIFACT\\u003e\\u003eCLIENT-DBRIEF\\u003c\\u003cARTIFACT\\u003e\\u003e\\n\\u003c\\u003cARTIFACT\\u003e\\u003ePESTLE-RESEARCH\\u003c\\u003cARTIFACT\\u003e\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c\\u003cSEARCHER\\u003e\\u003e\\n\\n"'\n- '"# PESTLE Strategic Insights\\n\\n## Prompt and Instructions for Claude Opus 4  \\n\\nYou\n  are a brand strategy analyst. Your task is to synthesise PESTLE insights based on\n  a brand’s context and relevant external factors.  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Brand Information  \\n-\n  **Product/Service:** {{Product/Service}}  \\n- **Mission/Vision:** {{Mission/Vision}}  \\n-\n  **Positioning:** {{Positioning}}  \\n- **Target Audience:** {{Target Audience}}  \\n-\n  **USP:** {{USP}}  \\n- **Competitors:** {{Competitor}}  \\n- **Reference Brands:**\n  {{Reference Brands}}  \\n- **Market Geography:** {{Market Geography}}  \\n- **Timeframe:**\n  {{Timeframe or assume next year}}  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## External Insights  \\nUse the following\n  external insights to contextualise your response:  \\n{{INSERT PESTLE TRENDS GATHERED\n  FROM PESTLE RESEARCH}}  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Task  \\nGenerate a PESTLE analysis with **20–75\n  unique insights**.  \\n\\n- **Structure** by PESTLE category  \\n- **Format:** plain\n  text bullet list  \\n- **Each insight:** 1–3 sentences  \\n- **No introduction or\n  summary**  \\n- Focus **only** on insights that affect **branding**, not general\n  operations  \\n- Where useful, refer to **audience expectations, communication strategy,\n  trust, cultural alignment, or social media relevance**  \\n\\n## Output Requirements  \\n-\n  Deliver the response **exclusively in valid Markdown**.  \\n- No citations, metadata,\n  or source markers.  \\n- Only bullet-pointed insights grouped under the six PESTLE\n  categories.  \\n\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Instructions\