h external authoritative sources (industry reports, academic research,\n  trend forecasters, government data, expert commentary) to ensure confidence and\n  applicability.  \\n\\n## Context & Methodology\\n\\nYou are conducting a PESTLE analysis\n  specifically through the lens of brand strategy and consumer engagement. Your research\n  must identify macro-environmental factors that directly or indirectly influence\n  brand perception, positioning opportunities, and strategic communication.\\n\\n###\n  Research Methodology:\\n1. **Source Diversity Requirements**:  \\n   - Minimum 3 source\n  types per PESTLE category from: industry reports, academic research, news media\n  (last 18 months), government data, trend forecasting firms, consumer surveys, expert\n  commentary  \\n   - Prioritize authoritative sources: McKinsey, Forrester, Gartner,\n  Pew Research, government statistics, peer-reviewed journals  \\n   - Include both\n  global perspectives and market-specific insights  \\n\\n2. **Temporal Framing**:  \\n\n  \\  - Current state: factors actively influencing the market now  \\n   - Emerging\n  (6-12 months): trends gaining momentum  \\n   - Future horizon (1-3 years): anticipated\n  shifts requiring preparation  \\n\\n3. **Brand Impact Assessment**:  \\n   Each insight\n  must clearly connect to one or more of:  \\n   - Brand perception/reputation  \\n\n  \\  - Consumer behavior changes  \\n   - Communication channel evolution  \\n   - Competitive\n  differentiation opportunities  \\n   - Brand experience transformation  \\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n  Brand Specifications\\n\\n### Brand Identity\\n- **Brand Name**: {{Brand Name}}  \\n-\n  **Industry/Sector**: {{Industry/Sector}}  \\n- **Brand Archetype**: {{Brand Archetype}}\n  \\ \\n- **Core Values**: {{Core Values}}  \\n- **Brand Purpose/Mission**: {{Brand Purpose/Mission}}\n  \\ \\n\\n### Market Position\\n- **Target Segments**: {{Target Segments}}  \\n- **Geographic\n  Markets**: {{Geographic Markets}}  \\n- **Competitive Set**: {{main_competitors}}\n  \\ \\n- **Market Position**: {{Market Position: leader/challenger/niche}}  \\n- **Price\n  Positioning**: {{Price Positioning: premium/mid/value}}  \\n\\n### Strategic Context\\n-\n  **Current Brand Challenges**: {{Current Brand Challenges}}  \\n- **Growth Objectives**:\n  {{Growth Objectives}}  \\n- **Innovation Areas**: {{Innovation Areas}}  \\n- **Brand\n  Heritage/History**: {{Brand Heritage/History}}  \\n- **Sustainability Commitments**:\n  {{Sustainability Commitments}}  \\n\\n### Consumer Relationship\\n- **Customer Journey\n  Stage Focus**: {{Select the Customer Journey Stage Focus: awareness/consideration/purchase/loyalty}}\n  \\ \\n- **Digital Maturity**: {{Select the Digital Maturity: traditional/hybrid/digital-first}}\n  \\ \\n- **Community Engagement Level**: {{Select the Community Engagement Level: passive/active/co-creative}}\n  \\ \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Request\\n\\nGenerate **exactly 20 insights per PESTLE category**\n  (120 total) that meet the criteria below:\\n\\n#### For each insight, provide:\\n1.\n  **Insight Title**: Clear, specific descriptor [Opportunity/Threat] [Short-term:\n  0-1yr/Long-term: 1-3yr] [Confidence: High/Medium/Low]  \\n2. **Detailed Paragraph**\n  including:  \\n   - Specific trend/factor description with quantitative data where\n  available  \\n   - Direct brand impact explanation  \\n   - Supporting evidence from\n  named sources  \\n   - Geographic/demographic specifics if applicable  \\n   - Connection\n  to brand's strategic context  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## POLITICAL FACTORS\\n\\n### P1: [Insight\n  Title] | Opportunity | Short-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph...]\\n\\n[Continue\n  P2–P20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ECONOMIC FACTORS\\n\\n### E1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity |\n  Long-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph...]\\n\\n[Continue E2–E20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n##\n  SOCIAL FACTORS\\n\\n### S1: [Insight Title] | Threat | Short-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed\n  paragraph...]\\n\\n[Continue S2–S20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## TECHNOLOGICAL FACTORS\\n\\n### T1:\n  [Insight Title] | Opportunity | Short-term | Medium Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph...]\\n\\n[Continue\n  T2–T20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## LEGAL FACTORS\\n\\n### L1: [Insight Title] | Threat | Short-term\n  | High Confidence\\n[Detailed paragraph...]\\n\\n[Continue L2–L20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ENVIRONMENTAL\n  FACTORS\\n\\n### EN1: [Insight Title] | Opportunity | Long-term | High Confidence\\n[Detailed\n  paragraph...]\\n\\n[Continue EN2–EN20]\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Metadata\\n- **Research\n  Date**: {{Today's date}}  \\n- **Primary Markets Analyzed**: [List of Primary Markets\n  Analyzed]  \\n- **Key Sources Consulted**: [List top 10 sources]  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## Quality\n  & Completeness Criteria\\n- Specificity over generalization  \\n- Evidence-based over\n  speculative  \\n- Brand-relevant over generic business impact  \\n- Actionable over\n  merely informational  \\n- Current and emerging over historical  \\n- **Completeness\n  Verification**:  \\n  - Confirm that all **six PESTLE categories** are present (Political,\n  Economic, Social, Technological, Legal, Environmental).  \\n  - Confirm that each\n  category contains **exactly 20 numbered insights** (P1–P20, E1–E20, S1–S20, T1–T20,\n  L1–L20, EN1–EN20).  \\n  - At the end of your response, include a short **Validation\n  Report** explicitly listing:  \\n    - Whether all categories are present  \\n    -\n  Whether each category contains 20 insights  \\n    - Any missing or incomplete sections\n  (should always be none)  \\n\\n<<SEARCHER>>\\n\\n<<PROMPT>>\\nWhat is client #{client}'s\n  Brand Name\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Industry/Sector\\nWhat is client #{client}'s\n  Brand Archetype\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Core Values\\nWhat is client #{client}'s\n  Brand Purpose/Mission\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Target Segments\\nWhat is client\n  #{client}'s Geographic Markets\\nWhat is client #{client}'s Main Competitors\\nWhat\n  is cl